[{"id":"VH966832","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div>\n<div class=\"stimulus_reference\">\n<div class=\"standalone_image\">\n\n<img alt=\"The figure presents a diagram of a sphere that suspended by an insulating string, shown hanging diagonally to the right, between vertical parallel plates. The left plate is positively charged and the right plate is negatively charged.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/VH966832.g12.png\"></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">The figure shows a sphere of mass <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"m\"><math alttext=\"m\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>m</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> with net charge <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"positive Q\"><math alttext=\"positive Q\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mo>+</mo><mrow><mi>Q</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> that is connected to an insulating thread. The sphere is suspended at rest between two oppositely charged parallel plates. Which of the following shows a correct free body diagram for the forces acting on the sphere?</p>","rubricRef":"VH966832_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"inline_image\"><img alt=\"The figure presents a free body diagram with three arrows extending from a common point. An arrow labeled F sub E points horizontally to the right, and arrow labeled m g points vertically downward, and a longer arrow labeled T points diagonally downward and to the right, bisecting the area created by arrows F sub E and m g.\" height=\"106\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/VH966832.g06.png\" width=\"100\"></span></p>\n","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"inline_image\"><img alt=\"The figure presents a free body diagram with three arrows extending from a common point. An arrow labeled m g points vertically upward. An arrow labeled F sub E points horizontally to the left, and a longer arrow labeled T points diagonally upward and to the left, bisecting the area created by arrows mg and F sub E. &nbsp;\" height=\"108\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/VH966832.g07.png\" width=\"100\"></span></p>\n","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"inline_image\"><img alt=\"The figure presents a free body diagram with three arrows extending from a common point. An arrow labeled m g points vertically upward. An arrow labeled F sub E points horizontally to the left, and a longer arrow labeled T points downward and to the right.\" height=\"122\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/VH966832.g08.png\" width=\"100\"></span></p>\n","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"inline_image\"><img alt=\"The figure presents a free body diagram with three arrows extending from a common point. An arrow labeled F sub E points horizontally to the right. An arrow labeled m g points vertically downward, and a longer arrow labeled T points upward and to the left.\" height=\"122\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/VH966832.g09.png\" width=\"100\"></span></p>\n"],"answer":3}]